{"type":"message","id":"a0b582c0","parentId":"f0ee9c05","timestamp":"2026-02-15T15:59:43.212Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sun 2026-02-15 17:59 GMT+2] OPERATION: REALITY CHECK & CI/CD DEBUG.\n\n1.  **Truth Finding (Logs):**\n    *   *Constraint:* I cannot browse the live GitHub web UI directly (auth wall/no browser tool auth).\n    *   *Action:* I will perform a **Deep Local Simulation** that mimics the GitHub Runner environment EXACTLY (Ubuntu, Clean venv).\n    *   *Hypothesis:* `orjson` often fails to build on bare runners without Rust/Cargo.\n    *   *Check:* Does `requirements.txt` force a binary wheel?\n\n2.  **Workflow Diagnosis (`ci-cd.yml`):**\n    *   *Read File:* `cat .github/workflows/ci-cd.yml`\n    *   *Check Paths:* Is `PYTHONPATH` set? Are `src/` files present before `pytest` runs?\n    *   *Check Naming:* Is it `ci-cd.yml` or `ci.yml`? (Badge link depends on this).\n\n3.  **Fix Implementation (Based on Failure):**\n    *   *Fix 1 (Deps):* Add `sudo apt-get install -y build-essential` (if compilation fails).\n    *   *Fix 2 (Path):* Ensure `PYTHONPATH` includes `${{ github.workspace }}/src`.\n    *   *Fix 3 (Rust):* If `orjson` needs compilation, add `actions-rs/toolchain` step (or use prebuilt wheels).\n\n4.  **Badges Check:**\n    *   Verify the URL in `README.md` matches the *actual* filename.\n\n5.  **Output:**\n    *   \"LOG ANALYSIS: [Simulated Failure Reason]\"\n    *   \"FIX APPLIED: [Code Change]\"\n    *   \"COMMIT: [Hash]\""}],"timestamp":1771171183211}}
{"type":"message","id":"3be7f5ed","parentId":"a0b582c0","timestamp":"2026-02-15T15:59:57.111Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Debugging the CI/CD**\n\nI'm starting to build a local simulation environment, mirroring the GitHub Actions CI/CD setup. The goal is to replicate the failure locally and pinpoint the root cause by closely examining the files and environment variables. The \"Deep Local Simulation\" idea seems like a great approach, aiming for a detailed reproduction.\n\n\n**Examining the Dependencies**\n\nI'm now investigating the `requirements.txt` file and planning to set up a clean Python virtual environment. I'll attempt to install the project dependencies, specifically paying attention to `orjson` and any other potentially problematic packages to understand if there are any build or compatibility issues. This should help to reproduce and troubleshoot the failure.\n\n\n"},{"type":"text","text":"I will start the investigation by reading the workflow file and `requirements.txt` to understand the environment and dependencies.\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771171196878_490","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":".github/workflows/ci-cd.yml"},"thoughtSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771171196986_491","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"requirements.txt"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771171197106_492","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"README.md"}}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":4897,"output":177,"cacheRead":2259,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":5074,"cost":{"input":0.009793999999999999,"output":0.002124,"cacheRead":0.00045180000000000003,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.012369799999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771171183212}}
{"type":"message","id":"897a8229","parentId":"3be7f5ed","timestamp":"2026-02-15T15:59:57.135Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771171196878_490","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"name: CI/CD Pipeline\n\non:\n  push:\n    branches: [ \"main\", \"dev\" ]\n  pull_request:\n    branches: [ \"main\", \"dev\" ]\n\npermissions:\n  contents: read\n\njobs:\n  linting:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v3\n      - name: Set up Python\n        uses: actions/setup-python@v4\n        with:\n          python-version: \"3.12\"\n      - name: Install dependencies\n        run: |\n          python -m pip install --upgrade pip\n          pip install flake8\n          if [ -f requirements.txt ]; then pip install -r requirements.txt; fi\n      - name: Lint with flake8\n        run: |\n          # stop the build if there are Python syntax errors or undefined names\n          flake8 . --count --select=E9,F63,F7,F82 --show-source --statistics\n          # exit-zero treats all errors as warnings. The GitHub editor is 127 chars wide\n          flake8 . --count --exit-zero --max-complexity=10 --max-line-length=127 --statistics\n\n  testing:\n    needs: linting\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    strategy:\n      matrix:\n        python-version: [\"3.12\"]\n    env:\n      DRY_RUN: true\n      PYTHONPATH: ${{ github.workspace }}\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v3\n      - name: Set up Python ${{ matrix.python-version }}\n        uses: actions/setup-python@v4\n        with:\n          python-version: ${{ matrix.python-version }}\n      - name: Install dependencies\n        run: |\n          python -m pip install --upgrade pip\n          pip install pytest\n          if [ -f requirements.txt ]; then pip install -r requirements.txt; fi\n      - name: Test with pytest\n        run: |\n          pytest\n\n  gitleaks:\n    name: Gitleaks\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v3\n        with:\n          fetch-depth: 0\n      - uses: gitleaks/gitleaks-action@v2\n        env:\n          GITHUB_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}\n\n\n  security:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    permissions:\n      actions: read\n      contents: read\n      security-events: write\n    strategy:\n      fail-fast: false\n      matrix:\n        language: [ 'python' ]\n    steps:\n      - name: Checkout repository\n        uses: actions/checkout@v3\n      - name: Initialize CodeQL\n        uses: github/codeql-action/init@v2\n        with:\n          languages: ${{ matrix.language }}\n      - name: Autobuild\n        uses: github/codeql-action/autobuild@v2\n      - name: Perform CodeQL Analysis\n        uses: github/codeql-action/analyze@v2\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771171197134}}
