{"type":"message","id":"2eb29e4f","parentId":"82d710e8","timestamp":"2026-02-15T15:59:57.148Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771171197106_492","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 🤖 DMarket Telegram Bot (High-Frequency Trading Edition)\n\n[![CI](https://img.shields.io/github/actions/workflow/status/Dykij/DMarket-Telegram-Bot/ci-cd.yml?branch=dev)](https://github.com/Dykij/DMarket-Telegram-Bot/actions/workflows/ci-cd.yml)\n[![License](https://img.shields.io/github/license/Dykij/DMarket-Telegram-Bot)](LICENSE)\n![Gitleaks](https://img.shields.io/badge/Gitleaks-Protected-brightgreen)\n![Latency](https://img.shields.io/badge/Latency-30ms-brightgreen?logo=speedtest)\n![Skills](https://img.shields.io/badge/Skills-CS2%20%7C%20Dota2%20%7C%20Rust%20%7C%20TF2-orange)\n![Arch](https://img.shields.io/badge/Arch-Event--Driven-blueviolet)\n![Activity](https://img.shields.io/github/commit-activity/m/Dykij/DMarket-Telegram-Bot)\n![Style](https://img.shields.io/badge/Code%20Style-Black-000000)\n\n> **Enterprise-grade automation** for DMarket interaction, featuring sub-millisecond latency and robust multiprocessing architecture powered by Gemini AI.\n\n---\n\n## ⚡ Performance Dashboard\n\n| Metric | Standard Bot | MyClawDev (HFT) |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Response Time** | `500ms` | **`0.03ms`** |\n| **Throughput** | `10 req/s` | **`1000+ req/s`** |\n| **Uptime** | `99.0%` | **`99.99%`** |\n\n---\n\n## 🧠 AI Stack\n\nWe leverage a dual-model approach for optimal performance:\n\n*   **Gemini Pro 1.5**: Handles complex reasoning, market trend analysis, and strategic decision-making.\n*   **Gemini Flash**: Dedicated to ultra-low latency execution for arbitrage opportunities and sniping.\n\n---\n\n## 🏗️ Architecture\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    Master[Master Controller] --> Redis[(Redis Message Broker)]\n    Redis --> CS2[CS2 Worker]\n    Redis --> Dota[Dota2 Worker]\n    Redis --> Rust[Rust Worker]\n    Redis --> TF2[TF2 Worker]\n    \n    style Master fill:#f9f,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px\n    style Redis fill:#ff9,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px\n    style CS2 fill:#bbf,stroke:#333\n    style Dota fill:#bbf,stroke:#333\n    style Rust fill:#bbf,stroke:#333\n    style TF2 fill:#bbf,stroke:#333\n```\n\n---\n\n## 📜 Version History\n\n*   **v2.1:** Docker, GHCR, Enterprise CI/CD.\n*   **v2.0:** Multiprocessing, 40 Skills, 0.03ms Latency.\n*   **v1.0:** SACS-2026, Ed25519, Hot Reload.\n*   **v0.1:** Legacy script (Broken Async).\n\n## 🎮 Commands\n\n### General\n*   👋 `/start` - Initialize the bot interaction.\n*   ❓ `/help` - Show available commands.\n*   📊 `/status` - Check system health and uptime.\n*   ⚙️ `/settings` - Configure bot preferences.\n\n### Trading\n*   💰 `/balance` - View current DMarket balance.\n*   📦 `/inventory` - List items in inventory.\n*   📉 `/price <item>` - Check price for a specific item.\n*   🛒 `/buy <item>` - Initiate a buy order.\n*   🏷️ `/sell <item>` - Initiate a sell order.\n\n### Automation\n*   🤖 `/auto_buy` - Toggle auto-buy module.\n*   🔄 `/auto_sell` - Toggle auto-sell module.\n*   📜 `/history` - View transaction history.\n*   🛑 `/stop` - Emergency stop all active tasks.\n\n---\n\n## 🚀 Deployment\n\n### Docker (Recommended)\n\n```bash\ndocker pull ghcr.io/dykij/dmarket-telegram-bot:latest\ndocker run -d --env-file .env ghcr.io/dykij/dmarket-telegram-bot:latest\n```\n\n### Manual\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/Dykij/DMarket-Telegram-Bot.git\ncd DMarket-Telegram-Bot\npip install -r requirements.txt\npython main.py\n```\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771171197147}}
{"type":"message","id":"4a5b66d1","parentId":"2eb29e4f","timestamp":"2026-02-15T16:00:22.868Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Evaluating the Files**\n\nI've got the `ci-cd.yml` file and am reviewing its contents. Currently, I'm focusing on the `PYTHONPATH` setting within the file. It's configured to point to the GitHub workspace. This is fine for a flat project structure, but I need to consider potential adjustments if the source code resides within a subdirectory like `src/`.\n\n\n**Examining the Dependencies**\n\nI'm now carefully examining the `requirements.txt` file. I've noted the specified packages, including `orjson`, `cryptography`, and `pydantic`. I've also identified a critical issue: a potential encoding problem towards the end of the file. This looks like a mix of text and binary, or a copy-paste error. This needs immediate attention.\n\n\n**Confirming the Structure**\n\nNow, I'm verifying the project structure. My immediate task is to determine if a `src/` directory exists. This is crucial for correctly configuring the `PYTHONPATH` in the CI/CD pipeline. I'll need to know this before making a decision on that.\n\n\n**Confirming and Adjusting**\n\nI've got the `README.md` file now, and I've verified the badge and link to the CI/CD workflow. This confirms the file path's correctness. However, I still need to verify the project structure and clean up the `requirements.txt` file as previously planned.\n\n\n"},{"type":"text","text":"I'll start by checking the file structure to verify the `PYTHONPATH` setting, and then I'll address the corruption in `requirements.txt`.\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771171222863_493","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"dir /B /S"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":12225,"output":955,"cacheRead":6402,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":13180,"cost":{"input":0.02445,"output":0.01146,"cacheRead":0.00